message.content:
**Analysis of the Main Target Image**

1. **Number of Blocks and Layers**  
   - The scene is composed of two separate “mini‐structures.” The left structure is a tall “tower” with two short vertical cylinders as “legs,” a rectangular platform spanning those legs, a red arch block on the platform, a yellow half‐cylinder on top of the arch, and two more vertical cylinders stacked behind forming the tall column, topped by an orange wedge.  
   - The right structure looks like a “cart,” with two horizontally oriented orange cylinders acting as wheels, a yellow rectangular block bridging those wheels, a blue cube on top of one end of the block, and a yellow half‐cylinder on the other end.

2. **Spatial Relationships (Left Structure)**  
   - Bottom layer: Two short orange cylinders stand vertically side by side (the “legs”) plus another stack of two orange cylinders behind them (the “tower”).  
   - Second layer: A horizontal yellow rectangular block (“platform”) rests on top of the two front cylinders and is also adjacent to the bottom cylinder of the tower.  
   - Third layer: A red arch block sits on top of the yellow platform. A yellow half‐cylinder rests on the arch’s flat upper face.  
   - The top of the tower: Two short orange cylinders are stacked vertically, with an orange wedge (small “roof”) capping the topmost cylinder.

3. **Spatial Relationships (Right Structure)**  
   - Bottom layer: Two short orange cylinders laid horizontally, parallel to each other (the “wheels”).  
   - Second layer: A horizontal yellow rectangular block bridging on top of these two wheels.  
   - Third layer: A blue cube sits on one side of that yellow block; a yellow half‐cylinder is placed on the other side.

---

**Matching Blocks from the Dictionary**

Below are the dictionary indices (in parentheses) and how many times each is used:

- **Orange short cylinder (vertical) – #7**: 4×  
  (2 for the front legs of the tower and 2 stacked to form the tall column behind)  
- **Orange cylinder (horizontal) – #9**: 2×  
  (the two “wheels” of the right‐hand structure)  
- **Orange wedge (roof shape) – #16**: 1×  
  (the small orange “roof” on top of the tall tower)  
- **Yellow rectangular block (horizontal) – #5**: 2×  
  (one bridging the two front legs on the left tower and one bridging the two horizontal wheels on the right)  
- **Yellow half‐cylinder (horizontal) – #10**: 2×  
  (one on top of the red arch, one on the “cart” next to the blue cube)  
- **Red arch block – #1**: 1×  
  (sits under the yellow half‐cylinder in the left structure)  
- **Blue cube – #4**: 1×  
  (the blue block on the right‐hand structure)

---

**Step‐by‐Step Assembly Order**

Use the blocks exactly as listed below (note that the same index may appear multiple times). A convenient build sequence would be:

{
  Step1: Move block with index 7   (left front leg)  
  Step2: Move block with index 7   (left right leg)  
  Step3: Move block with index 5   (yellow platform spanning the two legs)  
  Step4: Move block with index 7   (base of the tall tower behind)  
  Step5: Move block with index 7   (second tower cylinder stacked above)  
  Step6: Move block with index 16  (orange wedge “roof” on top of the tower)  
  Step7: Move block with index 1   (red arch on top of the yellow platform)  
  Step8: Move block with index 10  (yellow half‐cylinder on the red arch)  
  Step9: Move block with index 9   (first horizontal “wheel” of the cart)  
  Step10: Move block with index 9  (second horizontal “wheel” of the cart)  
  Step11: Move block with index 5  (yellow block bridging the two wheels)  
  Step12: Move block with index 4  (blue cube on one end of the cart)  
  Step13: Move block with index 10 (yellow half‐cylinder on the other end)
}

This completes the structure shown in the main target image without rotating any blocks beyond their dictionary orientations.
